<Author>vst08
<Content>Simple and comfortable with good location and friendly staff We enjoyed our stay at the Gutenberg, my brother and I just wanted somewhere clean and comfortable right in the centre. The Gutenberg was great value when compared to other hotels of similar location and standard. The room was also a good size and we were lucky enough to get a small balcony...although it rained all weekend! The staff were great, happy to advise and remembered your name and then greeted you by name each time we returned...that counts. Room was basic, with tiled floor and 2 single beds, it was very clean as was the bathroom. Breakfast was simple, cereal, toast or croissant, and the coffee suprisingly drinkable. Its less than a minutes walk from the Ramblas, Gothic Quarter and Port, making it a great base. 
