<Author>traveller1074
<Content>great location Just returned from a weekend break for my friends 50th birthday.There was 8 men in 1 double and 2 triple rooms. We all agreed that the Hotel was in a perfect location and it was a very good Hotel. The staff on the desk were very friendly, helpful and spoke good english. The Hotel had the feel of a family run Hotel as opposed to a corporate Hotel. Breakfast was served in a pleasant room and was quite adequate for us.I agree with some previous reviews, the surrounding streets can be a little intimidating at night, best to approach from main road and a quick left into reception, but I must say, we did not encounter any problems and we used the side streets to get to Hotel.The Ramblas is a 2 minute walk away and the marina is just 5 minutes away.All of us would stay at this Hotel without hesitation, again. 
