<Author>Todiscover
<Content>excellent location, and very friendly receptionist! I stayed in Gutenberg aparthotel Barcelona for 5 nights, from 19 to 25 December i think, and I loved the place!If you like simple, warm and clean places where u have all what u need, u'll love this hotel!Our first impression was great thanks to the friendly receptionist who spoke some arabic words!The streets in Barcelona were very cold, and when we get in the room, my friend and I were surprised, it was soooo waaaarm!!the room was very clean, with 2 twin confortable beds.there was a cupboard, but when we opened it we realized that it was a kitchen actually,lol (stupid country girls!!)there was all what you need to cook and eat in your room, there was a small fridge as wellthe bathroom was very simple but cleanbut what is amazing in this hotel is the location, it's in las Ramblas!! u can have fun all the time, do shopping, go to the passeo Maritimo, all this 5 to 20minutes walking from the hotelalso there is a metro station (green line) 2 minutes walk from the hotelIt's a cosy place when u can feel home!there is a Carrefour market about 10 minutes walk from the hotel, and also a popular market where u can buy a delicious fruit juce, and a lot of chocolate!!to go to Plaza Catalonia, Parallel, Gaudi museum, it will take 20min to 30min walk, or u can take the Metro (the green line), it will take u even to the Camp Nou (Reina Christina station) 
