<Author>jacquieuk1
<Content>very pleased considering reasonable rates We are a couple aged 45 years. We had a limited budget and found the rates for this hotel extremely good comparing to other hotels in the area. We travelled with Ryanair and used the transfer coach (21 euros return). From there we continued on the metro (4 stops) and stopped at Drassanes. From this stop the hotel was approx 2 mins. The position of this hotel is fantastic, just on a little street off the Ramblas situated at the port end. We did not find the hotel vicinity threatening or dangerous as other reviews have quoted. The hotel reception staff were very helpful, speaking good english and able to assist on a few trips we had planned to try. We had requested a double bed as most rooms are twin and were very happy to have a double bed in our room. The rooms were good sized with sofabed, kitchen with fridge/cooking facilities. Also bathroom complete with bath/shower/bidet/sink etc. (hot water always available). We also had a balcony but views were of the streets, though we still enjoyed watching the world go by with a bottle of wine. Breakfast was continental with a good choice of bread/ham/cheeses, yoghurts, cereals, omelletes, sausages, toast marmalade/jam etc. Also fruit juice, tea coffee available.We had read reviews regarding noise in the hotel and we noticed that there were groups of older school children who were a little noisy when leaving the rooms but the noise at night was fine. I had taken ear plugs after reading reviews but didnt use them.Our overall stay at this hotel was great, i cant really complain about any of it.If you want any info regarding the hotel please email me on jackiehuller@hotmail.com 
