<Author>EmmaHarrow
<Content>Hotel? Hostel ... This hotel will be OK if you don't intend to spend any time in it and plan on partying until the early hours every morning. If you want a quiet, relaxing hotel in which you can chill and get some sleep after a long days sightseeing please look elsewhere.The location is great, just off the Ramblas and a five minute walk from the port. There are some good offers around and rooms are quite cheap. Rooms are clean but basic. All this would be fine - apart from the noise. The hotel has small balconies overlooking a grotty street which the whole world seems to hang out on all night. You will be lucky to get an hours sleep unless you drink a few bottles of Cava first. The hotel is full of school parties who slammed doors and ran up and down the corridors from morning until night. Breakfast is alright, but the queues are so long you may consider going to a local cafe to guarantee a seat.I hate moany reviews but my heart did sink when it was time to go back to the hotel and it is sadly the worst I have ever been in.Barca is a great city and you will have a brilliant time. Maybe I'm just too old for this hotel . If you are eighteen then Gutenberg may be may be just right - otherwise stay somewhere else. 
