<Author>Livenjoy
<Content>Pratical If you don't intent to spend too much time in your hotel, this is a good option. I've been there for 4 days (from 7 to 10th of June), and it was a good decision. The hotel is situated near Ramblas, but not in the main road, so it seems a little strange on first approach. Nevertheless, you will not feel unsafe if you enter thru the main street (avoid the secondary streets, especially at night). If you already know Barcelona, and the Ramblas, you know that at night some precautions must be taken. Take the subway during day, and taxi at night. Positive: Price, Location (near rambla, subway station, maremagnum, columbus plaza - taxis), people friendly, clean.Negative: Near narrow secondary streets, noisy, poor room sound proof, no bar, and no restaurant (for dinner). The break-first is sufficient. The price compensate 70% of all negative aspects... 
