<Author>Mcginty75
<Content>Good basic hotel close to las ramblas This hotel can only be described as suitable for budget travellers. I stayed with some colleagues from work in September 2005. It served it's purpose well as a 'crash-pad' for a big night out in Barcelona.The hotel is located one block off the world famous Las ramblas (Plaza colon end). It is bordering the red light district so it can get a little dodgy later in the evening. In terms of situation the hotel is perfect for short breaks and stags or hens. The rooms are ensuite if a little cramped and the foyer is where they have spent most of their refurbishment budget, the lifts worked and there was minimal noise while we were there.There is a great little bar just beside the hotel to the left, a real sense of how the catalans enjoy life in their capital. Menu's of the day for 8 euro including 3 courses and a glass of wine of beer. Again basic but authentic.i hope you enjoy the best city in europe, I certainly did and am looking forward to getting back. 
